qProperty.markdown:
^[%[The **Reload Analyzer** is an application designed for Qlik Cloud to track and analyze application reloads within the tenant. Some of the benefits of this application are as follows:](4)](inherit)^[%[
](4)](inherit)^[%[**\- **](3)**Track number of reloads by type \(Scheduled, Hub, In App, API\) and by User**](inherit)^[%[**\- View all data connections of each application's most recent reload**](3)](inherit)^[%[**\- Find all applications that use a data connection**](3)](inherit)^[%[**\- Analyze concurrent reloads**](3)](inherit)^[%[**\- Track reloads by Spaces**](3)](inherit)^[%[**\- View all tasks and their respective statuses**](3)](inherit)^[%[**\- Tie alerts into metrics, \(e.g. a task has failed 5 times consecutively\)**](3)](inherit)^[%[**
**](3)](inherit)^[^[**This application:**](inherit)^[**\- pulls a max of 90 days of reload history, and will then continue to build from there incrementally using QVDs.**](inherit)^[**\- only looks at reloads for non\-distributed QS applications.**](inherit)^[**\- only looks at data lineage for each of the application's most recent reload.**](inherit)^[**\- should not be used as an audit application.**](inherit)](inherit)^[**%[_
_](2)**](inherit)^[**%[Endpoints:](3)**](inherit)^[^[reloads \- public, stable](inherit)^[audits \- public, stable](inherit)^[items \- public, stable](inherit)^[spaces \- public, stable](inherit)^[data\-connections \- public, stable](inherit)^[reload\-tasks \- public, stable](inherit)^[users \- public, stable](inherit)^[tenants \- public, stable](inherit)^[apps/{appId}/reloads/metadata/{reloadId} \- public, stable](inherit)^[data\-files/quotas \- public, stable](inherit)](inherit)

qFieldDefs: =ValueList('Data Last Reloaded','Incremental QVD Max Range','QVD Current Volume (in Days)','Current Version','Latest Version')

qDef.qDef:
=If(ValueList('Data Last Reloaded','Incremental QVD Max Range','QVD Current Volume (in Days)','Current Version','Latest Version')='Data Last Reloaded',TimeStamp(ReloadTime() + $(vReloadTimeDiffFromGMT)),
If(ValueList('Data Last Reloaded','Incremental QVD Max Range','QVD Current Volume (in Days)','Current Version','Latest Version')='Incremental QVD Max Range',TimeStamp('$(vMaxReloadAge)') & ' (' & $(vu_reload_rolling_range) & ' days)',
If(ValueList('Data Last Reloaded','Incremental QVD Max Range','QVD Current Volume (in Days)','Current Version','Latest Version')='QVD Current Volume (in Days)',Floor(Max({1}ReloadEndTime)) - Floor(Min({1}ReloadEndTime)),
If(ValueList('Data Last Reloaded','Incremental QVD Max Range','QVD Current Volume (in Days)','Current Version','Latest Version')='Current Version','v$(app_version)',
If(ValueList('Data Last Reloaded','Incremental QVD Max Range','QVD Current Volume (in Days)','Current Version','Latest Version')='Latest Version','$(vLatestVersion)')))))

qStringExpression.qExpr: ='Note that the AuditReloadLineage QVD should remain small, as it only stores the data connections for the most recent reloads per app.'
